<div id=ftn16>

<p class=MsoFootnoteText><a href="#_ftnref16" name="_ftn16" title=""><span
class=MsoFootnoteReference><span class=MsoFootnoteReference><span
style='font-size:13.0pt;font-family:"Garamond","serif"'>[16]</span></span></span></a>
For the idea of the classic in literature, Pfeiffer, <i>History of</i> <i>Classical
Scholarship</i>, 206-7; T. S. Eliot., <i>What Is a Classic?</i> (London: Faber
&amp; Faber, 1945) (Eliot’s answer to his own question here was Virgil); Frank
